  "repo_truth": "Fresh read-only review of the exact twenty-three-entry HCM-2.2 thrice-remediated planning subject. The subject is planning-only; no HCM-2.2 product or production definition byte has landed. Independently reproduce every exact schema/JCS/fingerprint/profile/intake/approval/recovery contract, compare live carriers and authority, and inherit no clean conclusion.",
  "allowed_scope": [
    "Remain read-only and replay the sorted twenty-three-entry manifest and aggregate fingerprint before review.",
    "Review every subject byte: 00, 04, 06, three immutable prior dispatches, SPEC, all exact contract/schema/vector/JCS fixtures, plan, unchecked todo, planning proof, and three remediation records.",
    "Read unchanged 01, 02, 03, 05, 07, 08, HCM-0.6 decision, selected HCM-2.1 record/packet/proof, exact live definition assets, and engine/compiler/flow/CLI/skill/template/test sources only as needed.",
    "Run bounded read-only manifest, Markdown/link, Git, handoff/schema, uniform-definition/exact-ref, literal-JCS/fingerprint, content-schema, profile-source, intake, approval-trust, immutable-lineage, transaction/lifecycle, byte-contract, cross-platform, determinism, security, bridge, and classification checks.",
    "Return findings first with exact file/line evidence through the built-in channel."
  ],
  "non_goals": [
    "No edits, staging, commits, new dispatches, global handoffs, ledger writes, or user task hops.",
    "No Rust, Cargo, production definitions, runtime fixtures/tests/product/generated-skill/pipeline, HCM-2.3+, Phase-3, SDK, Tauri, Substrate, contract, dock, or publication implementation.",
    "Do not invent alternate schema/intake bytes, fingerprint/ref behavior, approval/identity/registry trust, transaction visibility, lifecycle, renderer, migration, compatibility mode, bridge, or sibling-family scope.",
    "Do not treat prior findings/remediation, passing reproduction, or contingent planning status as proof that the twenty-three-entry subject is clean."
  ],
  "tasks": [
    "Invoke required skills in order, remain read-only, replay the exact twenty-three-entry manifest/aggregate, and return BLOCKED if any byte differs.",
    "Review findings first in Critical, Required, Optional, Nit order with exact file/line, violated authority, failure, smallest remediation, and missing or invalidated proof.",
    "Reproduce all five schema documents/entries, eleven literal JCS lines/vectors, complete profile source lists, record-schema versions, dependency graph, fingerprints, old-byte preservation, exact-ref acyclicity, package feasibility, and independent-encoder contract.",
    "Verify the full literal sixteen-row intake, schema/retained-field validation value, every leaf source, value-versus-quality-waiver rule, all-mode equivalence, and candidate basis.",
    "Verify authenticator registration/use feasibility, no-agent approval enforcement, registry bootstrap and current-promotion-anchored transition chain, exact class-authority pair mapping, multi-class/waiver coverage, additive approval lineage, and native refusal.",
    "Verify total pre-intent/target/partial-record/commit-marker recovery, create-new-or-equal immutable records, atomic authority visibility, basis equality, reader locking, lifecycle observation/clearance, and every crash boundary.",
    "Verify canonical/Markdown byte grammars/fixtures, C03/C04, product cutover, bridges, proof wall, deletion gates, CRITICAL impact warning, planning-only status, primary commit, and separate parent closeout.",
    "Return CLEAN only if no valid Critical or Required finding remains; otherwise CHANGES_REQUIRED or BLOCKED. Make no edits."
  ],
